    "analysis": "Executor's results show a system-wide uptick in socket metrics starting at ~2024-01-20T03:26:00Z affecting broker (rabbitmq, queue-master) and many DBs and services. Among the allowed candidate services (carts, catalogue, orders, payment, user) the earliest anomalies are socket breaches for catalogue and payment (earliest 03:26, anomaly_count=25). user has socket anomalies but starting later (~03:39). carts shows CPU/latency/mem anomalies later (~03:40) which look like downstream effects. Logs.error_count are useless (P95=0); some log.row_count anomalies exist (carts at 03:27, payment/orders at 03:32) but are smaller in magnitude.\n\nWhat can be derived so far: the incident appears to be a network/socket-layer problem that started ~03:26 and affected many infrastructure components (rabbitmq, DBs) and services. To pick the specific root-cause service among the five candidates we need a quantitative severity ranking (how far each candidate's metrics deviate from their global thresholds) because many socket metrics are equal to their P95 (which may be a borderline/false-positive). The next step should compute per-candidate deviation ratios to identify the single service with the largest and earliest deviation (the most likely root cause among the five).",
